JOHANNESBURG - The North Gauteng High Court has set aside a decision by National Director of Public Prosecutions, Shaun Abrahams, to withdraw charges against his deputy, Nomgcobo Jiba. The judgment also orders President Jacob Zuma to institute disciplinary procedures against Jiba and Special Director of Public Prosecutions Lawrence Mrwebi. READ:Â Gerrie Nel guns for Nomgcobo Jiba The ruling calls for an inquiry into their fitness to hold office. The order was made in favour of Freedom Under Law. Jiba and Mrwebi have been barred from performing any function at the prosecuting authority, pending their appeal at the Supreme Court. eNCA